# Basic Calculator (with switch-case) ‚Äì C Program
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
This C program functions as a simple calculator that performs addition, subtraction,  
multiplication, division, and modulus using a switch-case statement.  
It demonstrates user input, basic arithmetic operations, and control flow in C.  
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# FEATURES
1. Addition (+)  
2. Subtraction (‚àí)  
3. Multiplication (√ó)  
4. Division (√∑)  
5. Modulus (%)  
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# STEPS
1. Save the code as `calculator.c`  
2. Compile it using a C compiler (e.g., `gcc calculator.c -o calculator`)  
3. Run the program (`./calculator` or `calculator.exe`)  
4. Enter two numbers and select an operator  
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# CODE
#include <stdio.h>

int main() {
    double num1, num2;
    char op;

    printf("üßÆ Basic Calculator\n");
    printf("Enter first number: ");
    scanf("%lf", &num1);

    printf("Enter an operator (+, -, *, /, %%): ");
    scanf(" %c", &op); // Note the space before %c to capture any leftover newline

    printf("Enter second number: ");
    scanf("%lf", &num2);

    switch(op) {
        case '+':
            printf("Result: %.2lf + %.2lf = %.2lf\n", num1, num2, num1 + num2);
            break;
        case '-':
            printf("Result: %.2lf - %.2lf = %.2lf\n", num1, num2, num1 - num2);
            break;
        case '*':
            printf("Result: %.2lf * %.2lf = %.2lf\n", num1, num2, num1 * num2);
            break;
        case '/':
            if (num2 != 0)
                printf("Result: %.2lf / %.2lf = %.2lf\n", num1, num2, num1 / num2);
            else
                printf("‚ùå Error: Division by zero is undefined.\n");
            break;
        case '%':
            if ((int)num2 != 0)
                printf("Result: %d %% %d = %d\n", (int)num1, (int)num2, (int)num1 % (int)num2);
            else
                printf("‚ùå Error: Modulus by zero is undefined.\n");
            break;
        default:
            printf("‚ùå Invalid operator.\n");
    }

    return 0;
}
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Usage Tips
- Ensure valid input to avoid division/modulus by zero  
- Try wrapping this in a loop to perform multiple calculations  
- You can later extend it to support power, square root, or scientific functions  
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
